Interoperability=20
                        =
Forum</SPAN></H2></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></TD></TR>
              <TR>
                <TD=20
                style=3D"PADDING-RIGHT: 10px; PADDING-LEFT: 10px; =
FONT-SIZE: 11px; PADDING-BOTTOM: 10px; COLOR: #000; LINE-HEIGHT: 16px; =
PADDING-TOP: 10px; FONT-FAMILY: verdana, sans-serif"=20
                vAlign=3Dtop>
                  <P>The promise of interoperability is freedom of =
choice and=20
                  ease of integration =E2=80=93 the confidence that, =
regardless of which=20
                  best-of-breed software is chosen, it just works with =
existing=20
                  heterogeneous infrastructures. Customers are demanding =
it, and=20
                  vendors are working hard to deliver it. </P>
                  <P>But there is still work needed to fulfill this =
promise. To=20
                  solve the industry=E2=80=99s pressing interoperability =
problems,=20
                  businesses must all collaborate to identify key issues =
and=20
                  brainstorm solutions. To this end, Microsoft cordially =
invites=20
                  you to join the discussion on this <A=20
                  =
href=3D"http://forums.microsoft.com/MSDN/default.aspx?ForumGroupID=3D577&=
amp;SiteID=3D1">Interoperability=20
                  Forum</A>.</P></A>
                  <P>This forum contains three specific topic areas for=20
                  discussion and collaboration:</P>
                  <P style=3D"MARGIN-LEFT: 20px"><A=20
                  =
href=3D"http://forums.microsoft.com/MSDN/ShowForum.aspx?ForumID=3D2069&am=
p;SiteID=3D1">Interoperability=20
                  Conversations</A><BR>We invite you to visit this forum =
to=20
                  raise any general questions, identify issues or =
propose=20
                  solutions you have about interoperability in the =
marketplace.=20
                  Discussions amongst industry participants on =
interoperability=20
                  issues will ultimately help to create solutions that =
address=20
                  key issues.</P>
                  <P style=3D"MARGIN-LEFT: 20px"><A=20
                  =
href=3D"http://forums.microsoft.com/MSDN/ShowForum.aspx?ForumID=3D2070&am=
p;SiteID=3D1">Technical=20
                  Interoperability Scenarios</A><BR>This is a forum to =
discuss=20
                  technical interoperability issues and how they can be=20
                  resolved. Some examples of discussion topics include =
developer=20
                  tools and runtime; office productivity; systems =
management;=20
                  and security and identity management. </P>
                  <P style=3D"MARGIN-LEFT: 20px"><A=20
                  =
href=3D"http://forums.microsoft.com/MSDN/ShowForum.aspx?ForumID=3D2072&am=
p;SiteID=3D1">Achieving=20
                  Interoperability through Standards</A><BR>One way to =
achieve=20
                  interoperability is through the implementation of =
industry=20
                  standard technologies. While standards are not the =
only way to=20
                  enable interoperability, they are an important part of =
the=20
                  conversation. We encourage you to use this forum to =
start=20
                  conversations related to standardizing technologies =
and=20
                  implementing standards in products.</P>
                  <P>This Forum is intended to enable an open =
conversation about=20
                  interoperability among industry participants. =
Resources=20
                  related to specific Microsoft news and strategy, as =
well as=20
                  links to forums where you can address questions on =
Microsoft=20
                  products, protocols and documentation, can be found =
through=20
                  exploring the links below.</P>
                  <P>
                  <UL class=3Darticle>
                    <LI>For an overview of Microsoft=E2=80=99s =
Interoperability work,=20
                    visit: <A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/interop">http://www.microsoft.com/intero=
p</A>=20

                    <LI>To see the most recent Interoperability =
Principles=20
                    announcement, visit: <A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/presspass/press/2008/feb08/02-21ExpandIn=
teroperabilityPR.mspx">http://www.microsoft.com/presspass/press/2008/feb0=
8/02-21ExpandInteroperabilityPR.mspx</A>=20

                    <LI>For information about the Microsoft =
Communications=20
                    Protocol Program, visit: <A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/about/legal/intellectualproperty/protoco=
ls/mcpp.mspx">http://www.microsoft.com/about/legal/intellectualproperty/p=
rotocols/mcpp.mspx</A>=20

                    <LI>For product support at Microsoft, visit: <A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://support.microsoft.com/">http://support.microsoft.com/</A> =


                    <LI>For questions regarding promotion of modeling =
and=20
                    simulation interoperability and reuse for the =
benefit of a=20
                    broad range of Modeling &amp;Simulation (M&amp;S)=20
                    communities, visit <A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://www.sisostds.org/">http://www.sisostds.org/</A>=20

                    <LI>For an overview of Microsoft=E2=80=99s Standards =
work, visit: <A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/standards/">http://www.microsoft.com/sta=
ndards/</A>=20

                    <LI>For information on the Open Source =
Interoperability=20
                    Initiative, visit: <A=20
                    =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/opensource/interop/default.mspx">http://=
www.microsoft.com/opensource/interop/default.mspx</A>=20
                    </LI></UL>
                  <P></P>
                  <P><A =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/interop/forum/#">Top of=20
                  page</A></P>
