    <td valign=3D"top" style=3D"padding:10px;font-family: verdana, =
sans-serif;color:#000;font-size: 11px;line-height:16px;">
		<p>
The promise of interoperability is freedom of choice and ease of =
integration &#8211; the confidence that, regardless of which =
best-of-breed software is chosen, it just works with existing =
heterogeneous infrastructures. Customers are demanding it, and vendors =
are working hard to deliver it. </p>

<p>But there is still work needed to fulfill this promise. To solve the =
industry&#8217;s pressing interoperability problems, businesses must all =
collaborate to identify key issues and brainstorm solutions. To this =
end, Microsoft cordially invites you to join the discussion on this <a =
href=3D"http://forums.microsoft.com/MSDN/default.aspx?ForumGroupID=3D577&=
SiteID=3D1">Interoperability Forum</a>.</p>=20
</a>
<p>This forum contains three specific topic areas for discussion and =
collaboration:</p>





<p STYLE=3D"MARGIN-LEFT:20PX;"><a =
href=3D"http://forums.microsoft.com/MSDN/ShowForum.aspx?ForumID=3D2069&Si=
teID=3D1">Interoperability Conversations</a><br />
We invite you to visit this forum to raise any general questions, =
identify issues or propose solutions you have about interoperability in =
the marketplace. Discussions amongst industry participants on =
interoperability issues will ultimately help to create solutions that =
address key issues.</p>=20

<p STYLE=3D"MARGIN-LEFT:20PX;"><a =
href=3D"http://forums.microsoft.com/MSDN/ShowForum.aspx?ForumID=3D2070&Si=
teID=3D1">Technical Interoperability Scenarios</a><br />
This is a forum to discuss technical interoperability issues and how =
they can be resolved. Some examples of discussion topics include =
developer tools and runtime; office productivity; systems management; =
and security and identity management.=20
</p>
<p STYLE=3D"MARGIN-LEFT:20PX;"><a =
href=3D"http://forums.microsoft.com/MSDN/ShowForum.aspx?ForumID=3D2072&Si=
teID=3D1">Achieving Interoperability through Standards</a><br />
One way to achieve interoperability is through the implementation of =
industry standard technologies. While standards are not the only way to =
enable interoperability, they are an important part of the conversation. =
We encourage you to use this forum to start conversations related to =
standardizing technologies and implementing standards in products.</p>=20

<p>This Forum is intended to enable an open conversation about =
interoperability among industry participants. Resources related to =
specific Microsoft news and strategy, as well as links to forums where =
you can address questions on Microsoft products, protocols and =
documentation, can be found through exploring the links below.</p>
<p>

<ul class=3D"article">

<li>For an overview of Microsoft&#8217;s Interoperability work, visit:=20
<a =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/interop">http://www.microsoft.com/intero=
p</a></li>
<li>To see the most recent Interoperability Principles announcement, =
visit: <a =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/presspass/press/2008/feb08/02-21ExpandIn=
teroperabilityPR.mspx">http://www.microsoft.com/presspass/press/2008/feb0=
8/02-21ExpandInteroperabilityPR.mspx</a></li>
<li>For information about the Microsoft Communications Protocol Program, =
visit: <a =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/about/legal/intellectualproperty/protoco=
ls/mcpp.mspx">http://www.microsoft.com/about/legal/intellectualproperty/p=
rotocols/mcpp.mspx</a></li>
<li>For product support at Microsoft, visit: <a =
href=3D"http://support.microsoft.com/">http://support.microsoft.com/</a><=
/li>
<li>For questions regarding promotion of modeling and simulation =
interoperability and reuse for the benefit of a broad range of Modeling =
&Simulation (M&S) communities, visit <a =
href=3D"http://www.sisostds.org/">http://www.sisostds.org/</a></li>
<li>For an overview of Microsoft&#8217;s Standards work, visit: <a =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/standards/">http://www.microsoft.com/sta=
ndards/</a></li>
<li>For information on the Open Source Interoperability Initiative, =
visit: <a =
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/opensource/interop/default.mspx">http://=
www.microsoft.com/opensource/interop/default.mspx</a></li>

</ul>
</p>


<p><a href=3D"#">Top of page</a></p>
